{
  "strengths": "Strict adherence to synthetic-only constraints ensures zero risk of real data exposure. The checklist format effectively isolates boundary definition from execution, promoting safe theoretical planning.",
  "risks": "Abstract nature may lead to oversimplified decision trees that fail to account for complex real-world device states. Lack of practical validation could result in theoretical gaps when applied to actual scenarios.",
  "improvement": "Introduce varied synthetic device profiles (e.g., locked, encrypted, damaged) to stress-test the checklist logic. Add automated validation scripts to verify that no external actions or real data references are inadvertently included in the output."
}
